The Footype demo stores the diagram as raw SVG in the tiddler text (type `application/x-foo`).
The custom editor writes the SVG to the tiddler on Close/Done, and the preview reads from the text.
For the demo we preview via a data URI `<img src="data:image/svg+xml;utf8,...">`.
Note: If you later choose to render inline SVG markup, be mindful of XSS/security; prefer sanitization.

